# README for Jeff Miller's Thousand Parsec Sandbox
# Jeff Miller, 26-July-2008

An interactive demo of the name generator is available on Google
App Engine at:

   http://tpnames.appspot.com

------------------------------------------------------------------------

Contents:

./README -- this file

------------------------------------------------------------------------

./source -- source and sample data, exclusive of files specific to
            demonstration applications.

./source/tpnames          -- Thousand Parsec name generator 
./source/tpnames/names.py -- name generator
./source/tpnames/*.txt    -- name data files

------------------------------------------------------------------------

./appengine -- contains Google App Engine demo applications,
               duplicates source and adds driver and UI files.

./appengine/tpnames -- app to demonstrate the name generator

  How to run it with the local dev_appserver.py or via command line:
./appengine/tpnames/README

  App config:
./appengine/tpnames/app.yaml
./appengine/tpnames/index.yaml

  App UI:
./appengine/tpnames/index.django

  Core name generator.  This is the repurposeable bit:
./appengine/tpnames/names.py

  Variously flavored name sets as app input:
./appengine/tpnames/ellie-anne-kate.txt
./appengine/tpnames/gems.txt
./appengine/tpnames/greek.txt
./appengine/tpnames/middle-earth.txt
./appengine/tpnames/starwars.txt
./appengine/tpnames/persian.txt
./appengine/tpnames/tpnames.py
./appengine/tpnames/western.txt

  static files for serving (e.g. images):
./appengine/tpnames/static
./appengine/tpnames/static/favicon.ico -- because it's Thousand Parsec
